headline: If You Invested $10K In Iron Mountain Stock 10 Years Ago, How Much Would You Have Now?
summary: Iron Mountain (NYSE:IRM) is a global leader in information management services. The company's offerings include digital transformation, data centers, secure records storage, information management, asset lifecycle management, secure destruction and art storage and logistics. It is set to report its Q1 2025 earnings on May 1. Wall Street analysts expect the company to post EPS of $0.43, unchanged from the figure in the year-ago period.
